title: Non-irradiated melanocyte-derived exosomes 1
characteristics_ch1: cell type: Adult human epidermal melanocytes
treatment_protocol_ch1: The melanocytes were irradiated with UVB at doses of 30 mJ/cm2 or 60 mJ/cm2 once at a 24-h interval for three consecutive days and then cultivated for 3 days.
growth_protocol_ch1: Adult human epidermal melanocytes were grown in Melanocyte Medium, which contained melanocyte growth factors (Sciencell #2201), at 37 °C and 5% CO2.
extract_protocol_ch1: Melanocyte derived exosomes were isolated using differential centrifugation. Exosomal RNA was extracted by HiPure Liquid miRNA Kit/HiPure Serum/Plasma miRNA Kit (Megan, China).
extract_protocol_ch1.1: 50 ng exosomal RNA of each samples were used to prepare small RNA libraries by NEBNext® Multiplex Small RNA Library Prep Set for Illumina (NEB, USA) according to manufacturer’s instructions.
data_processing: Illumina Bcl2FastQ  software used for basecalling.
data_processing.1: Clean reads were obtained after remove of low quality reads and removing reads with 5' linker sequence, reads without 3' linker sequence, reads without the insert tag, reads with poly (A), and reads shorter than 17 nt.
data_processing.2: Total clean reads were mapped to the human reference genome using the bowtie aligner.
data_processing.3: miRDeep2 was used to identify known mature miRNA based on miRBase21 (www.miRBase.org) and predict novel miRNA. Databases of Rfam12.1 (www.rfam.xfam.org) and pirnabank (www.pirnabank.ibab.ac.in) were used to identify rRNA, tRNA, snRNA, snoRNA and piRNA
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text files include RPM/COUNT values for each Sample
data_processing.6: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Processed data file. Differentially expressed miRNAs in UVB irradiated melanocyte-derived exosomes (UVBM-exo) and non-irradiated melanocyte-derived exosomes (Mexo).xlsx
contact_institute: The First Affiliated Hospital, School of Medicine, Zhejiang University
